  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Chop most of your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate your <strong>ginger</strong>, then peel and grate your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Zest half your <strong>lime[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1652179193129-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1652179193129-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1652179193129-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1652179193129-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1652179193129-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water </strong>(this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p><p>Add your <strong>pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) to a bowl with the <strong>chopped mint</strong>, <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of<strong> </strong>the <strong>grated ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add the <strong>lime zest</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>to the bowl</p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then shape into 2 long sausages per person</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1652179195093-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1652179195093-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1652179195093-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1652179195093-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1652179195093-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> cold water to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652179198056-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652179198056-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652179198056-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652179198056-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652179198056-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, preheat the grill to medium-high</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into thin discs</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Push a <strong>skewer</strong> through each of the <strong>sausages</strong> and transfer them to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652179200903-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652179200903-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652179200903-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652179200903-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652179200903-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray under the grill for 10-12 min, turning once halfway through, or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your<strong> Vietnamese-style pork skewers</strong></p><p>Combine the juice of <strong>half </strong>your<strong> lime[s]</strong> in a bowl with your <strong>chilli relish</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>soy sauce</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) – this is your <strong>sweet chilli dip</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1652179204386-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1652179204386-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1652179204386-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1652179204386-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1652179204386-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced carrot</strong> and <strong>pepper strips</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly charred</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1652179206793-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1652179206793-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1652179206793-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1652179206793-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1652179206793-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once charred, reduce the heat to medium-high and add your <strong>red</strong> <strong>Thai curry paste</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, the <strong>remaining grated garlic </strong>and<strong> ginger</strong>, <strong>remaining lime juice</strong> and <strong>remaining soy sauce </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, drain then add your <strong>king prawns</strong>, <strong>mangetout </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[140ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[180ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min further or until the prawns are cooked through – this is your <strong>fragrant king prawn stir-fry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1652179209752-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1652179209752-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1652179209752-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1652179209752-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1652179209752-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>remaining chopped coriander </strong>into the <strong>fragrant king prawn stir-fry</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> fragrant king prawn stir-fry </strong>with the <strong>basmati rice</strong>,<strong> Vietnamese-style pork skewers </strong>and<strong> sweet chilli dip </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
